pageContext.claim: “We're lucky. You go to places like China, they don't have oil and gas. They don't have it under their -- they have to go buy it and then they devalue their currency and manipulate their currency. And that costs them a fortune to go out and buy it. They hurt themselves in the long run.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. China is among the world's leading producers of both oil and natural gas.
